# S.P.I.D.E.R.
Smart Patrol and Intelligent Detection Exploration Robot

## Overview

S.P.I.D.E.R. is an ESP32-based quadruped surveillance robot designed for remote monitoring and exploration. The system enables wireless browser-based control and live video streaming using an ESP32-CAM module.

The project integrates embedded control, IoT communication, and mechanical locomotion to create a compact surveillance robot platform.

## Features

- Wireless browser-based robot control
- Live video streaming using ESP32-CAM
- Quadruped locomotion using servo motors
- PCA9685 PWM driver for stable servo control
- IoT-enabled remote monitoring

## Hardware Components

- ESP32
- ESP32-CAM
- PCA9685 Servo Driver
- Servo Motors
- Li-Po Battery
- Quadruped Robot Frame

## System Architecture

User → Web Interface → ESP32 → PCA9685 → Servo Motors  
            ↓  
        ESP32-CAM → Live Video Stream

